<figureCitation id="5F818BF40D2675536BD8B2FB6681A7FB" box="[159,227,186,212]" captionStart="FIGURE 3" captionStartId="6.[151,257,1913,1937]" captionTargetBox="[223,1316,798,1878]" captionTargetId="figure@6.[218,1348,783,1910]" captionTargetPageId="6" captionText="FIGURE 3. Brassolis species, in dorsal (left) and ventral (right) views (except for C). (A &amp; B) Male and female B. isthmia from Panama. (C) Male B. isthmia from Costa Rica. (D) Male of granadensis from Colombia. (E) Detail showing head and proboscis of B. isthmia from Panama. (F &amp; G) Male and female B. astyra from Rio de Janeiro (Brazil). (H) Male B. astyra from Rio Grande do Sul (Brazil)." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/188451/files/figure.png" pageId="7" pageNumber="8">
